</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="019F6556FF900E3FFF52D403FAFEAFC5" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="493A36DDFF900E3FFF52D403FAFEAFC5" blockId="2.[151,1437,1039,1426]" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="7BF1EACFFF900E3FFF52D403FE91AE7E" bold="true" box="[151,266,1039,1065]" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Members of the species-group are similar to those of the 
<taxonomicName id="8E854D5EFF900E3FFC60D41CFBC8AE7E" authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Owada" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[933,1107,1039,1065]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khumbuensis">
<emphasis id="7BF1EACFFF900E3FFC60D41CFBC8AE7E" box="[933,1107,1039,1065]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">P. khumbuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group but are distinguished by the medial area which is of the same colour as the subbasal and the postmedial areas (in the 
<taxonomicName id="8E854D5EFF900E3FFAC3D438FF2EAE26" authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Owada" baseAuthorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khumbuensis">
<emphasis id="7BF1EACFFF900E3FFAC3D438FF2EAE26" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">P. khumbuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group, the medial area is darker than other areas of the forewing), the nearly straight antemedial line (it is sinuous in the 
<taxonomicName id="8E854D5EFF900E3FFEFFD470FE7CAEC2" authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Owada" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[314,487,1147,1173]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khumbuensis">
<emphasis id="7BF1EACFFF900E3FFEFFD470FE7CAEC2" box="[314,487,1147,1173]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">P. khumbuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group), and the smooth outer margin of the postmedial line which is dentate in the 
<taxonomicName id="8E854D5EFF900E3FFF18D4ACFE12AEEE" authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Owada" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[221,393,1183,1209]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khumbuensis">
<emphasis id="7BF1EACFFF900E3FFF18D4ACFE12AEEE" box="[221,393,1183,1209]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">P. khumbuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group. Additionally, the outer forewing margin of the 
<taxonomicName id="8E854D5EFF900E3FFB84D4ACFB7BAEEE" authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[1089,1248,1183,1209]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albosignata">
<emphasis id="7BF1EACFFF900E3FFB84D4ACFB7BAEEE" box="[1089,1248,1183,1209]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">P. albosignata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group is less wavy than in the 
<taxonomicName id="8E854D5EFF900E3FFE40D4C8FDABAE8A" authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Owada" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[389,560,1219,1245]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khumbuensis">
<emphasis id="7BF1EACFFF900E3FFE40D4C8FDABAE8A" box="[389,560,1219,1245]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">P. khumbuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group. The male genitalia of the species-group differ from those of the 
<taxonomicName id="8E854D5EFF900E3FFF52D4E4FE8BAF56" authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[151,272,1255,1281]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Mamestra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albirena">
<emphasis id="7BF1EACFFF900E3FFF52D4E4FE8BAF56" box="[151,272,1255,1281]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">P. albirena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8E854D5EFF900E3FFE80D4E4FE6BAF56" authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Owada" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[325,496,1255,1281]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khumbuensis">
<emphasis id="7BF1EACFFF900E3FFE80D4E4FE6BAF56" box="[325,496,1255,1281]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">P. khumbuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-groups by the markedly smaller clavi, the more prominent dorsal costal protrusion, the stronger setae on the cucullus forming a corona (absent in the 
<taxonomicName id="8E854D5EFF900E3FFC19D500FBCDAF72" authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[988,1110,1291,1317]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Mamestra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albirena">
<emphasis id="7BF1EACFFF900E3FFC19D500FBCDAF72" box="[988,1110,1291,1317]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">P. albirena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8E854D5EFF900E3FFB4BD500FAA0AF72" authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Owada" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[1166,1339,1291,1317]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khumbuensis">
<emphasis id="7BF1EACFFF900E3FFB4BD500FAA0AF72" box="[1166,1339,1291,1317]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">P. khumbuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
speciesgroups), the stronger asymmetry of digiti, the somewhat more elongate sacculi, and the aedeagus having more elongate carina and vesica. The female genitalia are characterized by the elongate ventral medial process of the antrum (the similar process is present only in 
<taxonomicName id="8E854D5EFF900E3FFD84D574FD4EAFC6" authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" box="[577,725,1399,1425]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pateikkaya">
<emphasis id="7BF1EACFFF900E3FFD84D574FD4EAFC6" box="[577,725,1399,1425]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="24">P. pateikkaya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but in the latter species it is conspicuously less elongate).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
